issue.title: Phase 3: AI Model Integration Hub
issue.body:
## Overview
Implement a comprehensive AI model integration hub that supports multiple providers and intelligent switching between models based on task requirements and availability.

## Technical Requirements

### Core Features
- **Multi-Provider Support**
  - OpenAI (GPT-4, GPT-3.5, DALL-E, Whisper)
  - Anthropic (Claude 3 Opus, Sonnet, Haiku)
  - Google (Gemini Pro, Bard, PaLM)
  - Local LLMs (Ollama, LlamaCPP, GPT4All)
  - Hugging Face models
  - Replicate API integration

- **Model Switching & Routing**
  - Intelligent model selection based on task type
  - Automatic fallback on rate limits or failures
  - Load balancing across providers
  - Context-aware model routing

- **Cost Optimization Engine**
  - Real-time cost tracking per request
  - Budget alerts and limits
  - Model cost comparison
  - Automatic switching to cheaper models when appropriate
  - Token usage optimization

- **Performance Benchmarking**
  - Response time tracking
  - Quality scoring system
  - A/B testing framework
  - Model comparison dashboard
  - Custom evaluation metrics

### Architecture Design
```typescript
interface ModelProvider {
  id: string;
  type: 'openai' | 'anthropic' | 'google' | 'local' | 'replicate';
  models: Model[];
  rateLimit: RateLimitConfig;
  pricing: PricingConfig;
  capabilities: ModelCapabilities[];
}

interface ModelRouter {
  selectModel(task: Task): Model;
  fallbackChain: Model[];
  costThreshold: number;
  performanceRequirements: PerformanceConfig;
}
```

### Implementation Details
1. **Provider Abstraction Layer**
   - Unified API interface
   - Standard request/response format
   - Error handling and retry logic
   - Connection pooling

2. **Cost Management**
   - Token counting for all providers
   - Real-time pricing updates
   - Budget allocation per team/project
   - Cost prediction before execution

3. **Performance Monitoring**
   - Latency tracking
   - Success/failure rates
   - Quality metrics
   - Provider uptime monitoring

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Support for at least 5 AI providers
- [ ] Automatic failover with <100ms overhead
- [ ] Cost tracking accuracy within 1% of actual bills
- [ ] Performance dashboard with real-time metrics
- [ ] API response time <50ms for model selection
- [ ] 99.9% uptime for routing service
- [ ] Complete unit test coverage (>90%)
- [ ] Integration tests for all providers
- [ ] Documentation for adding new providers

## Dependencies
- Redis for caching and rate limiting
- PostgreSQL for metrics storage
- Prometheus for monitoring
- Grafana for visualization

## Priority
**P0** - Critical for multi-model support

## Estimated Effort
3 weeks (2 developers)

## Technical Lead
@Elena_Volkov - Performance optimization critical for model switching

## Related Issues
- Links to authentication system
- Connects with billing system
- Requires monitoring infrastructure

# Fix parts detail data mapping with hybrid approach ## Summary This PR fixes a regression introduced in PR #3 where clicking the "部品詳細" (Parts Detail) button from the main table resulted in a "該当データの明細が見つかりませんでした。" (No corresponding data details found) error message and blank page. **Root Cause**: The previous fix removed the `findOrder()` function and replaced it with direct array indexing by `rowIndex`. However, the `normalize()` function in `SevenFieldsTable.tsx` transforms raw `uploaded-json` data into `working-rows-v1` format, stripping out parts arrays via `pickSevenFromOrder()`. This broke the 1:1 index correspondence between the two localStorage data structures. **Solution**: Implemented a hybrid data retrieval approach that: 1. **Restores the `findOrder()` function** for field matching on ["受注番号", "納入先番号", "出荷日"] 2. **Adds `getPartsForRow()` hybrid function** that tries direct indexing first (performance), falls back to field matching (reliability) 3. **Updates component state** to track both `rowIndex` (from URL) and `selectedRow` (from localStorage) 4. **Updates data flow logic** in `details` useMemo and `modifyTargetOrder` function to use hybrid approach ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human - [ ] **Test core functionality**: Click "部品詳細" buttons from main table for multiple rows, verify no errors and correct parts data displays - [ ] **Test edit functionality**: Edit part values (部品番号, 部品名, 数量, 売上単価) and verify changes persist correctly - [ ] **Test delete functionality**: Delete parts and verify data is properly removed from underlying storage - [ ] **Test with different data structures**: If possible, test with different data sets to ensure hybrid approach handles various formats - [ ] **Check browser console**: Verify no JavaScript errors during navigation and data operations **Recommended End-to-End Test Plan**: Load the application → Upload/process data → Navigate through main table rows using "部品詳細" buttons → Edit some part values → Delete some parts → Navigate back to main table → Verify all changes persisted correctly. --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% flowchart TD MainTable["src/app/components/

issue.title: Fix incorrect ART class spec offsets
issue.body:
This PR requires a new Frida build because it affects the internal system_server agent.

Closes
- https://github.com/frida/frida/issues/3533
  - https://github.com/frida/frida/issues/3525
  - https://github.com/frida/frida/issues/3527
  - https://github.com/frida/frida-core/issues/1165
  - https://github.com/ViRb3/magisk-frida/issues/62
 
---

As you can see this is a widespread issue. 

The issue is that the current code only accounts for the ART class layout based on the android sdk.
However, `libart.so` is shipped with the google security updates, that way you can have an Android 16 layout on Android 15.
This is why `pm uninstall com.google.android.art` is a "fix", although temporarily.

I fixed this by automatically detecting the offsets for the art class spec. By using a known class `java/lang/Integer` we can search for known fields / methods and find the necessary offsets that way.
